<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C9C0FD88FE70B601" bold="true" box="[136,462,587,614]" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8C885FD8FFD77B602" authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1844" box="[461,713,588,614]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adenoptera">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C885FD8FFD77B602" box="[461,713,588,614]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Euphorbia adenoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread weed, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="F31312BEFF96FFB8CD28FD8FFB09B602" box="[1120,1207,588,614]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Central America, the Carribean and South America. In the State of São Paulo the species is only known by specimens collected on roadsides.
</paragraph>
