<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF96FFB8C9F5FD76FD3BB7E4" blockId="3.[136,1452,587,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C9F5FD76FE13B6AB" bold="true" box="[189,429,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8C8E4FD76FD13B6AB" authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1844" box="[428,685,693,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adenoptera">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C8E4FD76FD13B6AB" box="[428,685,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Euphorbia adenoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8CA0CFD75FC68B6AB" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[836,982,693,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8CA0CFD75FC68B6AB" box="[836,982,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it in the cyathial glands appendages (well developed in 
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C8BEFD1AFD7EB696" box="[502,704,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8C8BEFD1AFD26B696" authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1844" box="[502,664,728,754]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adenoptera">E. adenoptera</taxonomicName>
vs.
</emphasis>
absent or inconspicuous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8CD40FD1AFB22B696" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1032,1180,728,754]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8CD40FD1AFB22B696" box="[1032,1180,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Both species have an inconspicuous growth of the pistillate flower’s pedicel, so that the fruit is exposed through an aperture between the two glands bearing bigger appendages in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8CB3AFCE3FCABB75D" authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1844" box="[626,789,799,825]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adenoptera">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8CB3AFCE3FCABB75D" box="[626,789,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">E. adenoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the subsessile fruit splits the involucre during its maturation in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8C86CFC80FE0AB738" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[292,436,834,860]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C86CFC80FE0AB738" box="[292,436,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8C889FC81FD01B738" authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1844" box="[449,703,834,860]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adenoptera">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C889FC81FD01B738" box="[449,703,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Euphorbia adenoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8CD57FC80FB11B738" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1055,1199,834,860]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8CD57FC80FB11B738" box="[1055,1199,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its purplish anthers (
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C9D9FCA4FF0EB7E4" box="[145,176,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">vs.</emphasis>
yellowish in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF96FFB8C80FFCA4FE66B7E4" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[327,472,870,896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thymifolia">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF96FFB8C80FFCA4FE66B7E4" box="[327,472,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">E. thymifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the seeds.
</paragraph>
